LUMPY SKIN DISEASE - BULGARIA (04): BOVINE, VACCINE CONSIDERED
**************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this update:
[1] Spread in Haskovo
[2] Vaccination contemplated

******
[1] Spread in Haskovo
Date: Tue 19 Apr 2016
Source: Focus Information Agency [edited]
http://www.focus-fen.net/news/2016/04/19/404141/dr-georgi-stankov-280-animals-are-affected-by-lumpy-skin-disease-in-bulgarias-haskovo-district.html


A total of 280 animals in 8 settlements in the region of Haskovo have been affected by lumpy skin disease, according to Dr Georgi Stankov, director of the Haskovo District Directorate of Food Safety Agency.

"These animals must be euthanized, and farmers will receive compensation for them," Dr Stankov said. "Mosquitoes, flies, and mites infect domesticated animals directly. The disease is transmitted quickly among animals, but it is not dangerous to humans. The 1st outbreak was discovered in the village of Voden. So far, 9 centres in 7 towns in Dimitrovgrad municipality and a village in the municipality of Haskovo have been established," Dr Stankov said.

--
